# 🍚 RiceVault

### Git for your KDE Plasma desktop configurations

*A failsafe backup & restore manager for KDE Plasma ricing.*

![Platform](https://img.shields.io/badge/Platform-KDE%20Plasma%206-blue)
![Python](https://img.shields.io/badge/Python-3.11+-3776AB?logo=python&logoColor=white)
![License](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-green)

</div>

---

## 📖 Overview

**RiceVault** is a strict, failsafe CLI manager designed specifically for **KDE Plasma 6** desktop customization.

Unlike **Timeshift**, **Btrfs snapshots**, or traditional backup tools, RiceVault focuses exclusively on your **desktop appearance**—allowing you to save, switch, and restore your "rice" without worrying about corrupting your current setup.

Whether you're an r/unixporn enthusiast or someone who enjoys experimenting with Plasma themes, RiceVault provides a safe way to manage your desktop configurations.

---

## ⚠️ The Golden Rule

> **RiceVault will never overwrite your current configuration without first creating an automatic Emergency Backup.**

If anything goes wrong after restoring a profile, you can always return to the exact state your desktop was in just moments before.

---

# ✨ Features

## 🖥 Interactive CLI

Built using **Typer** and **Questionary**, providing an intuitive wizard-driven experience.

---

## 📦 Smart Collection

Automatically collects important desktop components, including:

- `kdeglobals`
- `kwinrc`
- Plasma Panels
- Widgets
- Keyboard shortcuts
- Kvantum themes
- Wallpapers
- Custom desktop assets

---

## 🛡 Automatic Emergency Backups

Every restore operation creates a timestamped emergency snapshot before changing anything.

Example:

```text
Emergency-2026-07-15_16-20-52
```

No blind overwrites.

No accidental loss.

---

## 🗂 Isolated Vault

Everything is stored inside

```text
~/RiceVault
```

making it easy to:

- Sync with Git
- Upload to Google Drive
- Copy to external drives
- Share between computers

---

## 🖼 Desktop Preview

Automatically captures screenshots using **Spectacle** so you can visually identify your backups before restoring them.

---

# 📂 Project Structure

```text
~/RiceVault
│
├── Backup-2026-07-15_16-20-52
│   ├── config/
│   ├── themes/
│   ├── wallpaper/
│   ├── metadata.json
│   └── preview.png
│
├── Backup-2026-07-18_20-30-01
│
└── Emergency-2026-07-20_09-10-11
```

